  "doc_id": "19561",
  "text": "Our first method differs from classical retrieval paradigms by the virtue of decoupling document-query similarities from relevance estimation at the model level. This helps to account for the potential misleading nature of these similarities which might be due to adversarial effects. This is also an important difference between our model and previous work on using inter-document similarities. (See [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] for surveys). Another difference between our two proposed methods and a previous suite of methods that utilize inter-document similarities [CITATION_3] is treating inter-document similarities and queryindependent document-quality estimates, at the model level, as complementary types of information rather than as substitutable [CITATION_4] . Thus, our second (re-ranking) method essentially generalizes past approaches [CITATION_5] .",
